<br> [Focus on Critically Endangered shark species that occur in South Africa]{.underline}

Many of the global threatened shark species that occur in South Africa have broad global ranges and face varying pressure across their ranges. Some of the pressures shown in @fig-3 may not be prevalent in South Africa. @tbl-3 summarises the pressures on 12 Critically Endangered shark species, focusing on pressures in South African waters. The Critically Endangered soupfin shark (*Galeorhinus galeus*) still faces pressure from fisheries removals of more than 100 tonnes in South Africa alone.


